3. Gas Sensor (Theoretical Implementation) 

Connection 

Gas Sensor Pin     Raspberry Pi 
VCC                5V 
GND                GND 
DO                 GPIO22 

Theoretical Steps 
1. Connect the gas sensor module to the Raspberry Pi. 
2. Configure the digital output pin as input. 
3. Continuously monitor the gas sensor signal. 
4. Display detection status on the terminal. 

Python Code

import RPi.GPIO as GPIO 
import time 
 
GAS_PIN = 22 
 
GPIO.setmode(GPIO.BCM) 
GPIO.setup(GAS_PIN, GPIO.IN) 
 
try: 
    while True: 
        if GPIO.input(GAS_PIN): 
            print("Gas Detected") 
        else: 
            print("No Gas Detected") 
        time.sleep(1) 
 
except KeyboardInterrupt: 
    GPIO.cleanup() 

