(c) Trigger Actions Based on Sensor Threshold (Theoretical) 

In this experiment, automated device control is explained theoretically.

Example condition: 

If Temperature > 30°C 
        ↓ 
Turn Fan ON 
Else 
Fan OFF 

Python Code (Conceptual Example)

import RPi.GPIO as GPIO 
import Adafruit_DHT 
import time 
 
sensor = Adafruit_DHT.DHT11 
pin = 4 
FAN = 23 
 
GPIO.setmode(GPIO.BCM) 
GPIO.setup(FAN, GPIO.OUT) 
 
while True: 
    humidity, temperature = Adafruit_DHT.read_retry(sensor, pin) 
    if temperature is not None: 
      if temperature > 30: 
          GPIO.output(FAN, True) 
          print("Fan ON - High Temperature") 
      else: 
          GPIO.output(FAN, False) 
          print("Fan OFF - Temperature Normal") 

time.sleep(2) 

Expected Output 

Example terminal output: 

Temperature: 28 
Fan OFF - Temperature Normal 

Temperature: 32 
Fan ON - High Temperature 

This demonstrates how IoT systems can automatically respond to environmental conditions 
using sensor data. 
